Source: slaughter
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Steve Kemp <steve@steve.org.uk>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>> 5.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.8.3
Homepage: http://www.steve.org.uk/Software/slaughter/


Package: slaughter-client
Provides: slaughter
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libdigest-sha1-perl, libwww-perl, libtext-template-perl, perl-modules
Description: Automation tool to perform system administration remotely
 This package contains a client which will connect to a Slaughter server
 and fetch policies to execute.
 .
 The policies which are executed locally are expressive perl scripts
 with an additional set of helper primitives which allow:
 .
  * Copying files.
 .
  * Executing programs.
 .
  * Sending alerts.
 .
 There is no server package.
